caption: I love the service......! and the interior design......!
Awesome customer service
One of my favorite Dim Sum places! The service is fast and friendly. The food is absolutely delicious and fresh. Plus everything is reasonably priced. Absolutely loving coming here!
Great place, beautiful decor and friendly staff.
Went here for dim sum and some sichuan food. The ambience/vibe is somewhat on the higher end. Recommend the twice cooked pork if you like spicy food.
Quiet and pleasant atmosphere for wonderful late lunch on a Friday. Wait staff were attentive and courteous. Food was excellent so we will return to explore the menu more.
Great food for a great price and amazing service. They never disappoint me. Highly recommended!!
Minghin is always one of my favorite restaurants in Chicago :) And most important thing is... It seems very clean and safe ;)

I’ve been here a couple times and there’s not much to complain about. It sort of has a luxury, high-end vibe for a Chinese restaurant and the decor was nice. The food was good but it could have been a touch more creative. The menu seems to have a very traditional feel that reads like a who’s who of traditional Chinese dishes including some odd and exotic but authentic ones like deep-fried pigeon. Overall, I hope to go back here after the pandemic and when the weather warms up and try some more dishes/cuisine this restaurant has to offer. I also like that they provide you with hot tea if you wish (choice between water and tea but I get both) and a little tray of little finger foods like roasted peanuts and dry chow mein noodles that you can eat when you’re not focused on your main meal..
Amazing dim sum! Additionally, the ambiance is spectacular and very welcoming. They also have great boba smoothies. Would definitely recommend when looking for a dim sum restaurant.

(Translated by Google) I just picked up through the snowstorm and ate it deliciously. I picked one of the most popular menus and they were all delicious. It seems to be a taste that Koreans can also enjoy. The price is also reasonable. Highly recommend.  (Original) 방금 전 스노우스톰을 뚫고 픽업해와서 맛있게 먹었습니다. 가장 인기가 많은 메뉴들 중에서 골랐는데 모두 맛있었습니다. 한국사람들도 맛있게 먹을 수 있는 맛인듯 하네요.  가격도 적당하고요.  적극 추천합니다.

Above average chinese food! Ordered for pickup. Bbq pork and snow peas - 4/5, snow peas were not crispy Shrimp fried rice - 3/5, i got chicken fried rice :-( Mongolian beef - 4/5, delicious ! Mapo tofu - 4/5, if you’re a mapo connoisseur, this tastes on the sweet brown sauce side, if you’re into that.  I always recommend ordering directly from the restaurants.
Delicious food every visit - our favorite Chinese restaurant! The ambiance of this restaurant is gorgeous and excellent customer service!
Best dim sum I’ve had in Chicago so far. Every thing was great: food and service.
Wonderful flavors and great portion size! We really like their food. Best Chinese Dim Sum I've ever had. Highly recommend if you ever pass by Streeterville area. Michelin star is well deserved

The dim sum was 5 stars, it could not be better. The American-Chinese food (kung pao, general tsao, chow fun) were decent but overly sweet. That was off-putting. I would recommend this place for excellent dim sum but not the typical takeout dishes.

This restaurant is clearly one of the best restaurants in the town. Anytime I come there I am greatly glad. They always preserve their high standard service and high levels of food they provide. You have no doubt will love this place. Warmly recommended.
Great dim sum and outdoor seating. Good service and so glad for this new location!

Minghin Cuisine is my favorite Chinese food in Chicago. We ordered takeout from here and it was delicious. We ordered chicken and broccoli in brown sauce spicy, Mongolian beef spicy, and wonton soup. By the time we got home, the food was still piping hot and packed well. The chicken and broccoli was amazing. Perfect amount of spicy, delicious brown sauce, good quality chicken, and not greasy at all. The Mongolian beef was also very good with a delicious sauce and peppers and onions. The wonton soup was huge with like eight huge wontons with good meat inside. The broth was also tasty. I will definitely order from here again. Thank you!

My boyfriend and I travelled into Chicago from Pittsburgh. We stumbled upon this restaurant for a late night dinner that look a little busy and thought let’s give it a shot...keeping our fingers crossed they would take us with no reservation. We were immediately seated and the restaurant could not have been cuter. It was so quaint and we didn’t feel we were on top of other tables and guests. We order tea for the table...highly recommended. Great prices on beer and wine. And our dinner blew our minds...so flavorful and light. Not greasy in the least bit!! The wonton soup was amazing, beef skewers so tender and the seafood fried rice was just perfect. This was such a happy find for us walking the streets in Chicago. My only recommendation to the restaurant is maybe a little mood lighting...they were tad bright for 9 o’clock at night. But if we lived here, we would dine here quite often!
A favorite.  Order from here often.  Never disappointed.
The is easily the best dim sum place in Chicago. Their food is very delicious and their price is reasonable in the downtown of Chicago.

This is perhaps the worst Chinese food I’ve ever had. I was excited to have dim sum but ordered orange chicken and soups just in case. What a waste of money. The initial odor of the food was a turn-off but I decided to push through and try it... I honestly wish I could take that back because each bite continued to get worse and worse to the point that the food became inedible.  I have absolutely no idea how this place has such high ratings because it is just disgusting. I want a full refund because the experience as a whole left a bad taste in my mouth. Stay away, far far away.
Great authentic food, clean environment, and friendly staff, very attentive and the food was greaaaaaatttttt. Highly recommend

Excellent food!! This was my favorite restaurant that I went to in Chicago. The food was really good; seasoned well; and great portion sizes. We ordered a ton of food, such as chicken and american broccoli (with brown sauce), orange chicken, steak, house fried rice, etc. Will definitely come back when I'm next in town. Highly recommend.
Food is very very good. Nice ambience
Nice restaurant, great food. Stopping by there every time I am in the area.
Great dimsum options available here. The hits: siew mai, custurd bolo bun, roasted pork! The misses: chee cheong fun was too thick for my liking and the charsiew bun was soggy.
The whole place from the interior of the restaurant to the almond cookies you get when you leave were amazing! Definitely will be back on my next visit to Chicago! 😄
I cannot recommend this place enough. My friends and I have gone here probably over 10 times times in the last 3 months. Fantastic food, great friendly service and the portions are large.
Very good but not great
My son likes your shrimp rolls. Other food is good as well!
Lovely Place!! Delicious fried rice and orange chicken!! Waiter was speedy & attentive!!
0 stars. Worst food and overprice.
Best dim sum in the Streeterville area. Solid happy hour deals too. Staff is always very friendly.
Their food was ok. There are a lot better Chinese food places I would go to, but wanted to give this one a try. I would not go back to it personally.
The best sweet and sour pork so far.  Why? Not a traditional heavy batter. It's lightly coated, ridiculously crispy,  a little on the fatty side to add flavor.
Though, ambience is good, but food and service are average.
Fresh, tasty and excellent

I only gave it a one star bc I had too..they need to figure out their customer service. My wife ordered a drink and it never showed up. The food is less than average. You don't have just one server just a bunch of people running around. My opinion dont go here.
Went in twice for dim sum and both times satisfied!!!

Great food in a great location. It's like Russian Roulette with the wait staff as they tag team serving you, though. One's real nice, another indifferent, another one mean. But the outdoor dining and food allowed me to overlook it: For now. 😈

The service here today was exceptional. Very prompt and courtesy from the wait staff. It was our first time at the downtown location and the menu was disappointing, very limited versus Chinatown. The food was okay, some items were a miss while others were great. I’ll definitely return to try some more menu items!

Its a nice restaurant that has done a very good job of making sure that tables are spread out and socially distanced. The staff is very courteous and friendly. The food quantity is a lot for the price, but the food is average.

While their food is fine, the takeout service is bad. They can take up to 45 minutes to have the food ready for takeout in addition to the standard 25-35 minutes set for takeout time at ordering online. Not worth it for takeout. Please improve your service.
Great service,very courteous and friendly. Food was delicious. Large portions and tasty.
Excellent service. Even better food.  10/10 would recommend
Beautiful and clean restauran!.   My food was delicious and the service was outstanding!!!
Great food and very friendly staff. My favorite place for Chinese food in Chicago.

Clean environment. Employees are nice and friendly. However, the food was disappointing. I am so disappointed about Peking duck. We ordered half of duck and the portion was like appetizers. They gave us 20% discount but still not satisfactory. Fried rice, they didn’t taste fresh. My husband ended up throwing up at night.
Good selection of unusual small plates.  Very authentic Chinese cusine.

Finally!  We have been waiting FOREVER for a good Chinese restaurant in Streeterville, and Minghin is it!  Fabulous, authentic Chinese food...I used to go to Hong Kong and mainland China often...wonderful attentive service, nice people all trying hard to make your experience perfect.  First time at this new location, and it is great.  Very low prices, and very large portions. Go there!
Good dim sum and outdoor and indoor dining. Killer mi tia
Finally found a good Chinese restaurant

Really enjoyed this place.  Reasonable price for the food you get.  The waiter bring you a tablet which give you a picture and price of the food available.  Linda and i had potstickers, chicken fried rice and duck.
Very nice patio dining and dim sum. No soup dumplings tho!
I love minghin cuisine, My family and I have ordered more than 2 times. Especially the Lo mein. There is also this awesome protein dish They are ribs I think. 5 stars! Amazingggg 🥰

Great new place in Streeterville, they opened just before the quarantine and I've been so excited to try it and relieved they were able to reopen when the city did.  The food is authentic and every dish was delicious. Service was excellent in spite of the language barrier. We felt welcomed and left happy.

Discovered this place by accident with a friend while walking down on Ohio street. Being a lover of Asian food I was truly impressed with the selection of Dim sum and other great foods as well. Highly recommended!
Good service but food is really bad! Not recommended
very delicious dim sum
Ordered dumplings and chk Lowmein . Worst Chinese food ever . Dont waste your money at this business give it ti charity instead or the homeless guy at the corner.
Food and service was amazing.
(Translated by Google) Great foid  (Original) Great foid
Chinatown stalwart MingHin's new Streeterville Outpost. Cantonese fare at its best, plus Dim Sum all day long!
So happy we have a dim sum !!!! I can’t wait to be back!
Great for and service, very quick with the food and servers are very nice

Outstanding! Really enjoyed the food and the atmosphere ....  Really cool watching the staff work as a team and are very very positive and polite.  Food wasn't heavily like it is sometimes at Chinese Restaurants.  Great experience!
Best dim sum in Chicago

My experience at Minghin was just allright. We went for the lunch special. The restaurant itself is big, looks fancy, but is friendly. I found the food too salty and there were very few pieces of beef in the beef dish I ordered, and it wasn't worth the price of the lunch special menu.  I prefer Grandee Cuisine around the corner on Grand and St Clair (which for some reason right now has a google glitch-- if you search Grandee it shows up as Ming Hin though these are very different resturants!) google, help Grandee fix this hack!!
Great dim sum and place. The ambiance is very nice and decor is gorgeous. The pricing is very fair for a great service.
Good food, prices, and service. Very friendly and attentive staff. Clean and beautiful interior.
Good food and good service what more could you ask for?

This place lives up to the hype. It looks beautiful but it isn't a fine restaurant. The shrimp shumai and Pork bun are popular items. They are delicious. Minghin is one of my best favorite dim sum spots in Chicago. Good price, authentic food, good service and zero complaints
Grandee Cuisine is the best chinese i've had in the city!

Great atmosphere, very warm and modern.  Staff was friendly and was able to cater to our dietary needs.  Nice also to have discounted parking right next door.  Would recommend to anyone who has wanted to try Dim Sum but is intimidated by the crowds in Chinatown.  Also nice that it is close to many of the lakefront attractions (you get 4 hours of parking for 10 dollars!)
Great food.  Dim sum was awesome & staff very attentive & polite.   Would definitely come back again.

The interior is GORGEOUS of this spot first off and the modern vibe is awesome with the option to order off iPads at your table. Seems like they are still working out the kinks with the iPads as a few servers came over with items asking if they were ours but were not. The food was amazing and it has a cute patio which will be awesome in the summer! No soup dumplings which I would love to see here but overall great experience
Wow! Amazing! Food and service on point 100% Plus great interior decor. It looks so expensive, but it's not.  Great find!
Wow, this place looks amazing. The dim sum were really good and they came out really fast. The biggest problem is parking in Lakeshore North. Wish they have valet parking or validated parking.
High class decoration.very beautiful.foods are ok .price is too  expensive........
Ordered in, everything was very tasteful and good. Glad they are in the neighborhood.
